Linguine and Shrimp Fra Diavolo

3 tsp evoo
6-7 garlic cloves, peeled and smashed
2 lbs jumbo shrimp, peeled and deveined
salt and fresh pepper to taste
1/4 c celery
1/2 c chopped onion
34 oz crushed tomatoes
1 1/2 tsp crushed red pepper (or to taste)
1 tbsp capers, drained
8 fresh basil leaves, chiffonade
12 oz whole wheat, high fiber, or brown rice pasta

Bring a large pot of salted water to boil. While water is heating up, heat 2 tsp of oil in a large heavy skillet over medium heat. Stir in the garlic and cook until golden, ~ 1min. Add the shrimp and cook 2-3 min to brown butnot cook through; sprinkle with salt to taste. Transfer the shrimp to a plate, leaving the garlic in the pan. Add pasta to water and cook per package instructions for al dente. Add remaining tsp of oil and add the celery and onions; cook 2 min, then add tomatoes, season with salt and crushed red pepper and bring to a simmer. Lower the heat and let it simmer ~8-10 min. Add the shrimp and cook another minute or 2; remove from heat. Add the capers and serve in a large bowl over pasta topped with the basil. Can garnish with fresh black pepper and parmesan cheese.

Shrimp weight after peeled is ~ 1 1/2lbs


Nutrition:
Calories: 376.2
Fat: 4.8g
Protein: 29.5g
Carbohydrates: 54.5g
Fiber: 5.5g
Sugar: 6.6g
Sodium: 569.3mg
